<h2>Solar Incentives in San Antonio</h2>
<p>San Antonio solar customers can take advantage of several valuable incentive programs to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, which remains at 30% through 2032 before stepping down. Texas offers additional benefits including no state income tax on solar savings and property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning your home's increased value from solar panels won't increase your property taxes. CPS Energy provides net metering through their SolarHost program, allowing customers to receive retail rate credits for excess electricity fed back into the grid. While CPS Energy discontinued their solar rebate program in recent years due to high demand, the combination of federal tax credits, state tax benefits, and net metering still makes solar financially attractive for San Antonio homeowners.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in San Antonio</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in San Antonio, prioritize companies with proper Texas licensing, local experience, and strong warranties. Look for contractors licensed by the Texas Department of Licensing and Regulation (TDLR) with electrical contractor licenses, NABCEP-certified installers, and specific experience with CPS Energy interconnection processes. Top-tier companies should offer comprehensive warranties including 25-year panel performance warranties, 10-12 year equipment warranties, and at least 10 years of workmanship coverage. Request multiple quotes, verify insurance coverage, and check Better Business Bureau ratings and online reviews from San Antonio customers. Experienced local installers will understand Bexar County permitting requirements, HOA considerations common in San Antonio neighborhoods, and optimal system design for the hot-humid climate. Avoid door-to-door sales tactics and instead work with established companies that provide detailed proposals, energy production estimates specific to your roof orientation and shading, and transparent pricing without high-pressure sales techniques.</p>

